{"abstract": "J. C. Penney\u2019s share price took an unwarranted climb on Tuesday when it said it had hired Ron Johnson of Apple to eventually run the company.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/15/business/15views.html", "snippet": "J. C. Penney\u2019s share price took an unwarranted climb on Tuesday when it said it had hired Ron Johnson of Apple to eventually run the company.", "lead_paragraph": "Apple\u2019s reality distortion field has enveloped J. C. Penney. The department store chain poached Ron Johnson, the man behind Apple\u2019s stores, to be its eventual chief executive. The hiring helped lift J. C. Penney\u2019s market value by nearly a fifth, or $1.2 billion, before edging back a bit at the end of trading on Tuesday. It is true that Mr. Johnson also spent 15 years at the retailer Target, but Apple\u2019s halo looks too wide.", "print_section": "B", "print_page": "2", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2011/06/15/business/Views/Views-jumbo.jpg", "height": 973, "width": 1024, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}], "headline": {"main": "Apple\u2019s Hype Envelops Penney", "kicker": "Reuters Breakingviews", "content_kicker": null, "print_headline": "Apple\u2019s Hype Envelops Penney", "name": null, "seo": null, "sub": null}, "keywords": [{"name": "organizations", "value": "Penney, J C, Co", "rank": 1, "major": "N"}, {"name": "subject", "value": "Appointments and Executive Changes", "rank": 2, "major": "N"}, {"name": "subject", "value": "Shopping and Retail", "rank": 3, "major": "N"}, {"name": "organizations", "value": "Apple Incorporated", "rank": 4, "major": "N"}, {"name": "subject", "value": "Commodities", "rank": 5, "major": "N"}, {"name": "subject", "value": "Economic Conditions and Trends", "rank": 6, "major": "N"}, {"name": "subject", "value": "Japan Earthquake and Tsunami (2011)", "rank": 7, "major": "N"}], "pub_d